timing_use_latch_time_borrow(25.10)        timing_use_latch_time_borrow(25.10)

Name
       timing_use_latch_time_borrow

Syntax
       timing_use_latch_time_borrow

       {true | false}

       Default: true

       When  set  to  false,  does  not  consider time borrowing during timing
       analysis. Time borrowing is the amount of time borrowed by  a  previous
       logic.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

       Note:  The  timing_use_latch_time_borrow global should not be used with
       the setAnalysisMode command. Use this global only when the setAnalysis-
       Mode command is not available.  When  the  setAnalysisMode  command  is
       available,  use  the -timeBorrowing parameter to control time borrowing
       consideration.

